  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: **2.42.0-stable-d8d04663**\r\n\r\nOS & Version: **Ubuntu 20.04.5 LTS** \r\n\r\nErigon Command (with flags/config):\r\n```\r\nExecStart=/data/erigon/bin/erigon --chain=mainnet --metrics --torrent.download.rate=20mb --metrics.addr=0.0.0.0 --metrics.port=6060 --private.api.addr=0.0.0.0:9090 --pprof --pprof.addr=0.0.0.0 --pprof.port=6061 --datadir /data/erigon --http --http.api=eth,debug,net,trace,web3,erigon\r\n```\r\nChain/Network: **ETH mainnet**\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nI'm fetching internal transactions with `trace_block` and `trace_transaction` method from node for transaction [0x32572f8933466b75c387ef64a36cffc72a9c467e5680be031d3f419509920041](https://etherscan.io/tx/0x32572f8933466b75c387ef64a36cffc72a9c467e5680be031d3f419509920041/advanced). According to Etherscan, some internals should be marked with `Out of gas` error. To keep it simple, I'll focus on one, non-zero transfer only: \r\n\r\n- from: `0x00000000006c3852cbef3e08e8df289169ede581` \r\n- to: `0x6845bec79ca918e7d8c68bf3497f7ef748b9f008` \r\n- value 0.0990025 ETH (or `0x15fba3fcc602800`)\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nInternal transfer is not marked with error:\r\n```\r\n        {\r\n            \"action\": {\r\n                \"from\": \"0x00000000006c3852cbef3e08e8df289169ede581\",\r\n                \"callType\": \"call\",\r\n                \"gas\": \"0x6be3\",\r\n                \"input\": \"0x\",\r\n                \"to\": \"0x6845bec79ca918e7d8c68bf3497f7ef748b9f008\",\r\n                \"value\": \"0x15fba3fcc602800\"\r\n            },\r\n            \"blockHash\": \"0xecd5a6127c0f152b0b0f657939867aa42220610ed92fdb8703f3e16366c6b03a\",\r\n            \"blockNumber\": 16634562,\r\n            \"result\": {\r\n                \"gasUsed\": \"0x0\",\r\n                \"output\": \"0x\"\r\n            },\r\n            \"subtraces\": 0,\r\n            \"traceAddress\": [\r\n                3,\r\n                0,\r\n                8\r\n            ],\r\n            \"transactionHash\": \"0x32572f8933466b75c387ef64a36cffc72a9c467e5680be031d3f419509920041\",\r\n            \"transactionPosition\": 75,\r\n            \"type\": \"call\"\r\n        },\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behavior\r\nJust fetch traces for block/transaction\r\n```\r\ncurl --location --request POST 'http://YOUR_NODE' \\\r\n--header 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\r\n--data-raw '{\r\n\t\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\r\n\t\"method\":\"trace_transaction\",\r\n\t\"params\":[\r\n\t\t\"0x32572f8933466b75c387ef64a36cffc72a9c467e5680be031d3f419509920041\"\r\n\t],\r\n\t\"id\":1\r\n}'\r\n```\r\nI'm guessing Erigon is somehow not marking these errors correctly, as different explorers shows these internals as successful, for example [Blockchair](https://blockchair.com/ethereum/transaction/0x32572f8933466b75c387ef64a36cffc72a9c467e5680be031d3f419509920041)\r\n\r\nIf you fetch all transactions for `0x00000000006c3852cbef3e08e8df289169ede581` up to this block and calculate balance with traces marked with error as in Etherscan, the address balance in ETH will match with the one returned by the `eth_getBalance`. Otherwise, with what's returned from Erigon, balance does not match.",
